    {
      "id": "6c3dc82a_85cd1c37",
      "file_path": "csit/plans/cps/setup.sh",
      "patchset_number": 10,
      "line": 36,
      "message": "--quiet-pull\n1. Silences output related to pulling images unless an error occurs.\n2. Useful in scripts where we don’t want unnecessary logs.\n\n--detach (or -d)\n1. Runs containers in the background (detached mode).\n2. Without this flag, logs will be shown in the terminal, and the process will block.\n\n--wait\n1. This tells Docker Compose to wait until all containers are healthy before returning control to the script.\n2. It relies on the healthcheck configuration in our docker-compose.yml\n\nNote:\nIf a container does not become healthy, the command fails, preventing issues later in the script.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
      "updated": "2025-02-12 17:33:20.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "aac2f537_f777fbee",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "1fa99f2d_766987c3",
      "file_path": "csit/plans/cps/setup.sh",
      "patchset_number": 10,
      "line": 36,
      "message": "Spot on!\n\nWithout --quiet-pull, you will see large amounts of useless logging:\n\n    15:33:54  686a76acd3c2 Downloading [===========================>                       ]  316.6MB/581MB\n    15:33:54  686a76acd3c2 Downloading [===========================>                       ]  324.6MB/581MB\n    15:33:55  686a76acd3c2 Downloading [============================>                      ]  333.6MB/581MB\n    15:33:55  686a76acd3c2 Downloading [=============================>                     ]  346.5MB/581MB",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2025-02-12 17:41:59.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "aac2f537_f777fbee",
      "unresolved": true
    },
