    {
      "id": "8e3f84cb_23bf1774",
      "file_path": "docker-compose/docker-compose.yml",
      "patchset_number": 12,
      "line": 50,
      "message": "\"pg_isready -d $POSTGRES_DB -U $POSTGRES_USER || exit 1\"\n\npg_isready without parameters checks the default database, but if we are using a custom DB, specifying it ensures proper validation.\n\n|| exit 1 → Ensures failure if pg_isready reports the DB is unavailable.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
      "updated": "2025-02-12 17:56:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "30be981b_118d28d0",
      "file_path": "docker-compose/docker-compose.yml",
      "patchset_number": 12,
      "line": 52,
      "message": "Reduce timeout (from 60s to 30s)\n\nIf the database doesn’t respond within 30 seconds, it’s likely unresponsive.\n60 seconds is excessive—containers should fail fast and retry instead.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
      "updated": "2025-02-12 17:56:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "8a977e98_d6e03b18",
      "file_path": "docker-compose/docker-compose.yml",
      "patchset_number": 12,
      "line": 54,
      "message": "Add start_period (15s)\n\nPrevents unnecessary failures while PostgreSQL is initializing.\nWithout this, health checks may fail too soon, causing unnecessary container restarts.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
      "updated": "2025-02-12 17:56:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "d9500008_dbbe3239",
      "file_path": "docker-compose/docker-compose.yml",
      "patchset_number": 12,
      "line": 92,
      "message": "|| exit 1\"\n\nEnsure Failure on Healthcheck Failure\n\n|| exit 1 → Explicitly fails the health check if grep does not find \"status\":\"UP\".\nWithout exit 1, Docker may not properly detect failure.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
      "updated": "2025-02-12 17:56:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "119b1010_0cf9b644",
      "file_path": "docker-compose/docker-compose.yml",
      "patchset_number": 12,
      "line": 109,
      "message": "Question If we should use :\n\n\"curl -fs http://localhost || exit 1\"\n\nUse curl Instead of service nginx status\n\nservice nginx status only checks if the Nginx process is running, but doesn’t verify if it's serving requests properly.\n\ncurl -fs http://localhost ensures Nginx is actually responding to HTTP requests.\n\n-f (fail silently on HTTP errors) and -s (suppress output) improve reliability.\nIf Nginx is down, the command will fail, making it a more accurate check.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
      "updated": "2025-02-12 17:56:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
