      "line": 137,
      "message": "kafka-topics --bootstrap-server kafka:29092 --list || exit 1\"\n\nUse kafka-topics --list Instead of kafka-cluster cluster-id\n\nkafka-cluster cluster-id only checks if Kafka can return a cluster ID, but it doesn’t verify if Kafka is fully functional.\n\nkafka-topics --list checks if Kafka can communicate with the brokers and list topics, ensuring it's operational.\n\nIf Kafka is down, this command will fail.",
